scripts.text: Accounts

W E Pickett

Director

Dankness and humidity are your first impressions as you emerge from the stairway. In the dim light, you see that this level of the tower is overgrown with bulbous plants. The tiled floor has been cracked and broken by the burrowing of sinuous roots.

For a moment you have the oddest feeling, as if you had just walked into a crowded room where people who were talking about you have just fallen silent. But the chamber is empty...

The susurration growns louder, and you pause to listen...

A chill runs down your spine as it suddenly resolves into a word... a name....

... i m o g e n ...

The sinister vegetation chokes this level thicker than ever... stalks and bulbs sway gently, leaves and creepers stir slowly, vines and tendrils furl and unfurl. A sibilant rustle becomes apparent at the edge of your hearing.
